---
interface Props {
  kicker: string
  title: string
  summary: string
}

const { kicker, title, summary } = Astro.props
---

<section class="relative py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24">
  <div class="pointer-events-none absolute inset-0 overflow-hidden">
    <div class="absolute left-1/2 top-0 h-64 w-full max-w-5xl -translate-x-1/2 rounded-full bg-violet-500/8 blur-3xl"></div>
    <div class="absolute -left-16 bottom-0 h-56 w-56 rounded-full bg-blue-500/10 blur-3xl"></div>
  </div>

  <div class="relative mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
    <div class="mx-auto max-w-3xl text-center">
      <p class="text-sm font-semibold tracking-[0.2em] text-violet-200 uppercase">{kicker}</p>
      <h1 class="mt-5 text-4xl font-bold text-white sm:text-5xl font-pj">{title}</h1>
      <p class="mt-6 text-lg leading-8 text-gray-300">{summary}</p>
    </div>

    <div class="mt-14 grid gap-8 lg:grid-cols-[0.9fr_1.1fr]">
      <div class="rounded-[2rem] border border-white/10 bg-[#131821] p-8 shadow-2xl shadow-black/20">
        <p class="text-sm font-semibold tracking-[0.18em] text-gray-400 uppercase">Tradeoffs</p>
        <div class="mt-8 space-y-4">
          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-emerald-400/20 bg-emerald-500/8 p-5">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">What this keeps</h2>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-gray-200">Astro 6, Cloudflare adapter, Starlight docs, Tailwind v4 website styling, and localized route fan-out.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="rounded-2xl border border-rose-400/20 bg-rose-500/8 p-5">
            <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-white">What this removes</h2>
            <p class="mt-3 text-sm leading-7 text-gray-200">Most business logic, content volume, API fetches, and translation plumbing that are unrelated to the CSS manifest leak.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>

      <div class="grid gap-6 sm:grid-cols-2">
        <article class="group rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-linear-to-br from-[#1a202a] to-[#12161c] p-7 transition hover:border-sky-400/30">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.18em] text-sky-200 uppercase">Route graph</p>
          <h2 class="mt-4 text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Many flat pages</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-gray-300">The production repo is not a tiny brochure site. The repro now reflects that with a broader website route surface.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="group rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-linear-to-br from-[#1a202a] to-[#12161c] p-7 transition hover:border-violet-400/30">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.18em] text-violet-200 uppercase">CSS graph</p>
          <h2 class="mt-4 text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Dense utility usage</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-gray-300">Cards, gradients, oversized blurs, timelines, and side panels all push more shared CSS into the build.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="group rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-linear-to-br from-[#1a202a] to-[#12161c] p-7 transition hover:border-emerald-400/30">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.18em] text-emerald-200 uppercase">Docs isolation</p>
          <h2 class="mt-4 text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Expected behavior</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-gray-300">Only docs routes should receive the Starlight base chunk and component chunk.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="group rounded-3xl border border-white/10 bg-linear-to-br from-[#1a202a] to-[#12161c] p-7 transition hover:border-amber-400/30">
          <p class="text-xs font-semibold tracking-[0.18em] text-amber-200 uppercase">Failure signal</p>
          <h2 class="mt-4 text-2xl font-semibold text-white">Manifest leak</h2>
          <p class="mt-4 text-sm leading-7 text-gray-300">When `/` or another website route gets `index@_@astro-*.css`, the repro has matched the real issue.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<style>
  article {
    position: relative;
    overflow: hidden;
  }

  article::after {
    content: '';
    position: absolute;
    inset: auto -20% -40% auto;
    width: 10rem;
    height: 10rem;
    border-radius: 9999px;
    background: radial-gradient(circle, rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.14), transparent 65%);
    opacity: 0;
    transition: opacity 180ms ease;
  }

  article:hover::after {
    opacity: 1;
  }
</style>
